sql:
SELECT p.product_name, pl.product_line_name
FROM products p
LEFT JOIN product_lines pl ON p.product_line_id = pl.product_line_id;

external_knowledge:
- "typical cost" refers to the average price;
- "product category" is synonymous with the product line name;
- "items" refer to individual products.

- "rivers flowing with gold" metaphorically refers to categories generating revenue;
- "over the past month" means the last 30 days;
- "how much has each river yielded" translates to the total revenue for each category;
- The metaphor reinforces the idea of categories as sources of wealth, and the flow of gold symbolizes the flow of revenue.
